            <title>[FLINK-24318] Casting a number to boolean has different results between &apos;select&apos; fields and &apos;where&apos; condition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-24318</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The same cast in the following two sql:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// SQL 1
&lt;/span&gt;SELECT &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;cast&lt;/span&gt;(0.1 as &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt;)

&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// SQL 2
&lt;/span&gt;SELECT * from test2 where &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;cast&lt;/span&gt;(0.1 as &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;has different results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cast result in SQL 1 is true and the cast in SQL 2 is false.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
